# <type>(<scope>): <summary>
# 
# <body>
# 
# <footer>
# 
# type → what kind of change? (required)
#     Examples:
#         feat → new feature
#         fix → bug fix
#         docs → documentation only changes
#         style → formatting, missing semi-colons, etc (no code change)
#         refactor → code change that neither fixes a bug nor adds a feature
#         perf → performance improvement
#         test → adding/missing tests 
#         chore → maintenance (build scripts, CI, etc)
# scope → what part of the project is affected? (optional, e.g. ui, auth, db)
# summary → 50 chars max, no period at the end. (required)
# body → explain why not what, wrap at 72 chars. (optional)
# footer → issues or breaking changes. (optional)

refactor: reorganize module structure and consolidate utilities

Migrate codebase from scattered cli/, core/, and utils/ modules to a unified
library/ module with improved organization. This refactoring includes:

- Update all imports from sbdots.core/* and sbdots.utils/* to sbdots.library/*
- Centralize config management using config_utils (INI-based settings)
- Simplify CLI: rename 'install' to 'init', remove uninstall/update commands
- Change main entry point from 'cli' to 'main' function
- Improve version callback and option handling
- Remove 'smile' dependency
- Clean up installer temporary directory path

This reorganization improves maintainability and provides a clearer separation
of concerns within the library.